column1: BEVERLEY HULL BRIDGE, SOUTH BULLOCK PUMPING STATION
# The February 1947 figure is identified on the sheet as a part-estimate due to snow and has been retained.
# The rain gauge location is actually South Bullock Pumping Station; this is about 1km north of Hull Bridge.
# Some of the sheets refer to the South Bullock location by name; it also fits the Tickton church directions.
# The rain gauge is marked on the 1910 OS 25 inch map.
# The grid reference shown on the 1950s sheet is for Hull Bridge itself and so is not the rain gauge location.
# The station continued until 1970 according to MIDAS.
